  "text": "For generating reconstructions the images were first aligned automatically using 5 or 10 nm gold colloid (British Biocell International, Cardiff, UK) deposited on one or both sides of the sections before data collection. The average alignment error was 1.3 pixels (range, 0.9 -2.2) root mean square. The reconstructions were made by a weighted backprojection method. Both the alignment and reconstruction algorithms are in the unified software package EM3D [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ; http://em3d.org). The spatial resolution in reconstructions generated from datasets collected at 31,000؋ to 62,000؋ magnification, which were used for making the surface models, was 2-3 nm for high-contrast structures such as the cytoplasmic and extracellular layers of the plasma membrane [CITATION_3] .",
